<br>
I close my eyes now, reminiscing my first trip to the surface lands. Land of the fey, home of the fairer races. To them, am I nothing more than a mockery; a macabre parody of their woodland culture? I did not know -- nay -- I do not know.<br>
<br>
Regardless, the memory still burns brightly within me. I remember my young accomplice to the surface lands, Keeyorll, a mistress of House Zo'Hryn. What energy that woman had! A master of the night, she escorted me, for my first time, to the dreaded surface, both to quench my curiosities, and because my training required it.<br>
<br>
We arrived in what I now know as the East Commonlands at dawn. This was the first time that I had ever seen the mighty ball of fire that I was later told, was known as &quot;the sun&quot;.<br>
<br>
Kee motioned towards me. &quot;Do not look at the fire.&quot; I say nothing, but instead eye the various ... creatures ... that wandered the land.<br>
<br>
&quot;Disgusting,&quot; I murmured to myself, staring at a small group of pale adventurers. Almost instantly, my vision was overtaken by the &quot;sun&quot;, the wreched ball of fire. Though it was merely daybreak, I could feel my blood boil, my skin crackle.<br>
<br>
And so, I ran with every bit of energy that I could muster up in my small body. Tall reeds and sunflowers scratched my delicate skin as tears flowed from within my bloodshot eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Release me!&quot; I scream to the sky, at no one in particular. The fire -- so bright and unwelcoming. I claw at my face, running even faster; blood runs freely from my chin.<br>
<br>
&quot;Release me!&quot; I yell at the ground as I topple over into a mound of wildflowers. My robe rips as I struggle to free myself from a bush of thorns.<br>
<br>
The chilling wind ran through my hair as I threw my arms up in exasperation. &quot;RELEASE ME!&quot; I holler at the top of my lungs. Blood was dripping down my robe, and yet, I did not care. Suddenly, my vision darkened and I felt nothing.<br>
<br>
I found myself in my bedchambers.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I cried.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreadie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DreaDie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/10/01 10:06:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Mother's Wisdom.</span><hr size=1> Dunno where your taking this, but I like what I read so far. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Edgie, sexy 40th level rogue</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukourinneelahn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kourin Nee lahn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/11/01 11:10:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My Mother's Wisdom.</span><hr size=1> It's not going anywhere, really. :)  It's little flashbacks of Kourin's life that I write .. when I should be doing homework.  Doh. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousebythefireplace>By The Fireplace</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
